      "description": "The Contractor shall support NASA in the completion of the refurbishment, modification, integration, test and verification of the SOFIA Airborne System through completion of Airworthiness flight test and flight certification. The Contractor shall work in concert with the Telescope Assembly Contractor, the Science and Mission Operations Contractor and NASA to plan the Airborne System integration and test effort. Execution of Phase One will be at the contractors facility in Waco, Texas. The Contractor shall identify any unsuitable systems or parts on Government Furnished Equipment for which the Contractor has prime responsibility and replace or repair them as required. The Contractor shall complete all work that the Contractor has pending as changes under contract NAS2-97001 that are subsequently approved by the SOFIA Program Control Board. The Contractor shall complete inspections required, reconditioning, maintenance and modification of the SOFIA aircraft, Boeing 747 SP serial number 21441. The work shall be done in accordance with the NASA approved list of Airworthiness Directives (ADs) and Service Bulletins (SBs) and with the FAA approved SOFIA-Boeing Maintenance Plan. The 747 shall be refurbished to comply with NASA Airworthiness for Public Use which are equivalent to FAA certification standards, FAR Part 25. The Contractor shall support the development of a NASA approved maintenance plan to support the aircraft for a expected service life of twenty years. Prior to NASA final acceptance of the fully operational Aircraft System, the Contractor shall conduct an inspection program in accordance with NASA, FAA and aircraft industry standards for major maintenance/overhaul of passenger aircraft, including, applicable requirements of aging fleet aircraft. The contractor shall be responsible for all aircraft maintenance through the aircraft ferry flight to NASA for the start of flight testing. All aircraft maintenance shall be completed in compliance with the Interim SOFIA Maintenance Program for First Flight. The Interim SOFIA Maintenance Program Plan for First Flight shall be developed and submitted for approval and shall include the FAA approved maintenance plan for the basic aircraft with modification. The performance of all aircraft maintenance shall be subject to the oversight, review and approval of NASA. The Contractor shall provide all labor, materials, and verification associated with the performance of required routine maintenance on the aircraft, during completion of the development and integration and test phases prior to ferry of the Airborne System to NASA. The Contractor shall complete development of, and shall obtain FAA acceptance of plans and procedures consistent with an experimental airworthiness document prior to first flight. The Contractor shall provide all labor, materials, and verification associated with the performance of required non-routine preventive and corrective maintenance on the aircraft, during completion of the development and integration and test phases prior to ferry of the Aircraft System to NASA. Non-routine maintenance is defined as the repair of structural damage, replacement of defective parts that are not included in the approved scheduled maintenance program, and incorporation of NASA approved SBs, and ADs. The Contractor shall complete fabrication, installation, integration, and verification of modifications to the 747 SP that was started under contract NAS2-97001. The Contractor shall support NASA in the completion of the refurbishment, modification, integration, test and verification of the SOFIA Airborne System through completion of Airworthiness flight test and flight certification. The Contractor shall work in concert with the Telescope Assembly Contractor, the Science and Mission Operations Contractor and NASA to plan the Airborne System integration and test effort. Execution of Phase One will be at the contractors facility in Waco, Texas."
