      "description": "IGF::OT::IGF NRA(NASA RESEARCH ANNOUNCEMENT) QUALIFICATION OF FORMAL METHODS TOOLS  1.0 INTRODUCTION/BACKGROUND:NASA''S AVIATION SAFETY PROGRAM IS CONDUCTING RESEARCH DIRECTED AT IMPROVING THE SAFETY OF CURRENT AND FUTURE AIRCRAFT OPERATING IN THE NATIONAL AIRSPACE SYSTEM. THE RESEARCH FOCUS INCLUDES THE SYSTEM-WIDE SAFETY ASSURANCE TECHNOLOGIES (SSAT) PROJECT. UNDER SSAT, THERE IS A TECHNICAL CHALLENGE AREA KNOWN AS ASSURANCE OF FLIGHT CRITICAL SYSTEMS (AFCS). A PRIMARY THRUST OF AFCS RESEARCH IS ADVANCING FORMAL METHODS TECHNOLOGY SO IT CAN SERVE THE NEEDS OF THE AVIONICS COMMUNITY.IN JANUARY 2012, THE RADIO TECHNICAL COMMISSION FOR AERONAUTICS (RTCA) RELEASED SEVERAL DOCUMENTS, PRODUCTS OF RTCA SPECIAL COMMITTEE SC-205, WHICH ARE KEY TO THE FUTURE OF CERTIFICATION OF AVIONICS SOFTWARE. FOREMOST AMONG THESE ARE DO-178C, SOFTWARE CONSIDERATIONS IN AIRBORNE SYSTEMS AND EQUIPMENT CERTIFICATION, AND DO-278A, SOFTWARE INTEGRITY ASSURANCE CONSIDERATIONS FOR COMMUNICATION, NAVIGATION, SURVEILLANCE, AND AIR TRAFFIC MANAGEMENT (CNA/ATM) SYSTEMS. AS THE SUCCESSORS TO DO-178B AND DO-278, THESE DOCUMENTS PROVIDE UPDATED GUIDANCE FOR DEVELOPERS OF AIRBORNE AND GROUND-BASED SOFTWARE.SC-205 ALSO CREATED FOUR SUPPLEMENTS TO ACCOMPANY DO-178C AND DO-278A. ONE OF THESE, FORMAL METHODS SUPPLEMENT TO DO-178C AND DO-278A, HAS BEEN PUBLISHED AS DO-333. FOR THE FIRST TIME, AVIONICS DEVELOPERS WILL HAVE EXTENSIVE GUIDANCE ON APPLYING FORMAL METHODS TECHNOLOGY TO PRODUCE EVIDENCE THAT CERTIFICATION AUTHORITIES CAN ACCEPT FOR CERTIFICATION CREDIT. THIS WILL PROVIDE A PATHWAY FOR THE GRADUAL INTRODUCTION OF FORMAL METHODS INTO THE DEVELOPMENT LIFE CYCLE AND THE EVENTUAL CERTIFICATION OF AIRCRAFT AND ENGINES WHOSE SOFTWARE AIRWORTHINESS IS ASSURED (IN PART) BY FORMAL METHODS.WHILE THE RELEASE OF DO-333 IS AN IMPORTANT EVENT, THERE REMAIN SIGNIFICANT CHALLENGES TO THE SUCCESSFUL INFUSION OF FORMAL METHODS INTO DEVELOPMENT AND CERTIFICATION WORKFLOWS. CHIEF AMONG THESE IS THE NEED TO QUALIFY ANY TOOLS USED TO PRODUCE CERTIFICATION EVIDENCE. ANOTHER SUPPLEMENT TO DO-178C AND DO-278A IS DO-330, SOFTWARE TOOL QUALIFICATION CONSIDERATIONS. THIS DOCUMENT ELABORATES THE GENERAL REQUIREMENTS THAT APPLICANTS MUST MEET WHEN USING SOFTWARE TOOLS IN THE GENERATION OF CERTIFICATION EVIDENCE.USE OF FORMAL METHODS TOOLS IS RELATIVELY NEW IN SOFTWARE CERTIFICATION. MOREOVER, THESE TOOLS MAKE USE OF MATHEMATICALLY RIGOROUS ANALYSES AND TYPICALLY INCLUDE SOPHISTICATED HEURISTIC SEARCH ALGORITHMS. AS A RESULT, THERE ARE QUESTIONS ABOUT HOW TO APPLY THE DO-330 GUIDANCE TO THIS CLASS OF TOOL. THERE IS A NEED TO IDENTIFY AND EXAMINE THE ISSUES SURROUNDING THE APPLICATION OF DO-330 TO FORMAL METHODS TOOLS SO THAT THEIR INTRODUCTION INTO THE CERTIFICATION DOMAIN CAN PROCEED AS SMOOTHLY AS POSSIBLE.IN ADDITION TO THE SPECIFIC REALM OF DO-330, THERE IS ALSO THE MORE GENERAL QUESTION OF FORMAL METHODS TOOL ASSURANCE, WHICH HAS RECEIVED LIMITED ATTENTION BY RESEARCHERS IN THE PAST. THE EMERGENCE OF A CERTIFICATION ROLE FOR FORMAL METHODS, ALBEIT ONE LIKELY TO REMAIN LIMITED INITIALLY, LEADS NATURALLY TO RESEARCH QUESTIONS ABOUT MORE ADVANCED APPLICATIONS OF THE TOOLS. 2.0 SCOPE OF WORK: THE SCOPE OF THE INVESTIGATION INCLUDES BOTH THE GENERAL PROBLEM OF ACHIEVING CONFIDENCE IN FORMAL"
