      "description": "IGF::OT::IGF  NASA RESEARCH ANNOUNCEMENT AWARD UNDER ROSES 2012. THE EUCLID PROGRAM TO STUDY THE COSMIC INFRARED BACKGROUND. EFFORTS UNDER THIS CONTRACT INCLUDE AN INNOVATIVE STUDY OF THE COSMIC INFRARED BACKGROUND (CIB) WITH EUCLID.  LIBRAE WILL EXPLOIT PLANNED EUCLID IMAGING OF BOTH THE WIDE AND DEEP SURVEY REGIONS AT INFRARED AND VISIBLE WAVELENGTHS IN ORDER TO:  1) MEASURE THE SOURCE-SUBTRACTED CIB STRUCTURE (FLUCTUATIONS) OUT TO SCALES OF A FEW DEGREES WITH BETTER THAN #tilde#1% ACCURACY.  THIS WILL ESTABLISH THE ABILITY TO CLEARLY DISTINGUISH THE NATURE AND PARAMETERS OF THE POPULATIONS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE PRODUCTION OF THE CIB FLUCTUATIONS.  2) DETERMINE THE LYMAN BREAK, AND EPOCHS, OF THE POPULATIONS PRODUCING THESE FLUCTUATIONS BY EXPANDING THE SED OF THE MEASURED FLUCTUATIONS.  3) CROSS-CORRELATE THE MEASURED FLUCTUATIONS WITH OPTICAL, IR, X-RAY, AND MICROWAVE IMAGING FROM A NUMBER OF OTHER FACILITIES. THESE INCLUDE BOTH THE SPITZER/IRAC AND HST/WFC3+ACS INSTRUMENTS, TO HELP CHARACTERIZE STELLAR (NUCLEOSYNTHETIC) SOURCES OF THE CIB FLUCTUATIONS. EFFORTS ALSO INCLUDE CROSS-CORRELATING WITH IMAGING FROM COEXTENSIVE X-RAY OBSERVED FIELDS, IN ORDER TO MEASURE THE CONTRIBUTION OF BLACK HOLES (AGN AND OTHER GRAVITATION OR ACCRETION-POWERED SOURCES) AMONG THESE SOURCES TO THE X-RAY BACKGROUND. CROSS-CORRELATING THE NEAR-INFRARED EUCLID CIB MAPS WITH PLANCK SUB-MM CIB AND CMB MEASUREMENTS WILL PROBE THE DUST EMISSION FROM THESE SOURCES AND CONSTRAIN ANY THERMAL SZ COMPONENT CONTRIBUTION. LIBRAE WILL THUS IDENTIFY THE NET EMISSIONS FROM THE FIRST STARS ERA, LEAD TO A BETTER UNDERSTANDING THE CONDITION OF INTERGALACTIC MEDIUM AT THAT EPOCH, ISOLATE THE CONTRIBUTIONS FROM THE FIRST BLACK HOLES AND SHED LIGHT ON DUST CONTENT AT THOSE TIMES. THE PROJECT HAS POTENTIALLY TRANSFORMATIVE IMPLICATIONS FOR UNDERSTANDING THE EMERGENCE OF THE UNIVERSE OUT OF THE \\DARK AGES\\\". IT IS WELL ALIGNED WITH EUCLID MISSION OBJECTIVES.\""
